    ],
    "notes": "Detection should focus on (1) process.executable path outside System32/Program Files loading user32.dll — especially from ProgramData, AppData, or Temp; (2) unsigned or unknown binaries calling SetWindowsHookEx via user32.dll load; (3) the combination of user32.dll ImageLoad (EID 7) + subsequent file creation in the same non-standard directory is high-fidelity for keylog output staging. Tune out: osk.exe, accessibility tools (narrator.exe, magnify.exe), known AV/EDR vendors, and input method editors (IME) from System32. Correlate EID 1 + EID 7 (user32.dll) + EID 11 from same PID for highest confidence."
  },
